98
00:09:08,879 --> 00:09:10,720
Then you would be the one they fall in love with.

99
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,090
Lan Qi, no way.

100
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:16,240
Yes, otherwise, why don't I even have a girlfriend...

101
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,399
when you've already divorced three times?

102
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:19,399
You'll lose friends if you talk like that.

103
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,759
Let's go eat our barbecue.

104
00:09:23,090 --> 00:09:24,120
Come.

105
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,210
Come on.

106
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,720
You're not hungry?

107
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:29,919
No.

108
00:09:30,759 --> 00:09:31,960
Stop grilling and eat.

109
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,120
Let's have a drink.

110
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:40,330
- Here. - Thank you.

111
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:52,120
Do you want some alcohol?

112
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:54,639
No.

113
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:55,799
I don't drink on the job.

114
00:09:58,879 --> 00:10:00,720
Fine. I won't drink if you won't.

115
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,720
I'll stay on the same channel as you.

116
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,450
Drink.

117
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,759
Everyone's enjoying themselves. You should relax.

118
00:10:09,210 --> 00:10:10,799
No. If you won't drink,

119
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,879
how can we talk when we're not on the same channel?

120
00:10:14,919 --> 00:10:16,159
I won't drink.

121
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:20,559
Give me some time. You will.

122
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:22,960
Here.

123
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:27,480
From what I've heard,

124
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,720
you're a great cook.

125
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:32,330
It's all right.

126
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:34,480
I can handle a small gathering of 10 people.

127
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:38,090
Then telling my dad you can't cook the other day was an act?

128
00:10:38,559 --> 00:10:39,720
It wasn't an act.

129
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,039
Old people are like children. You have to coax them.

130
00:10:46,330 --> 00:10:47,720
You really haven't changed at all.

131
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:51,600
Remember you had a nickname when you were a kid?

132
00:10:54,799 --> 00:10:56,399
I remember. Chameleon.

133
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,120
But I don't hate it.

134
00:10:59,799 --> 00:11:02,159
I didn't have a good dad...

135
00:11:02,159 --> 00:11:03,879
or a proper background.

136
00:11:04,159 --> 00:11:06,159
I camouflage myself...

137
00:11:06,159 --> 00:11:07,240
to achieve my goals.

138
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,320
I'm not embarrassed about it.

139
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:13,200
Is that your law for success?

140
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:15,679
One of them.

141
00:11:22,039 --> 00:11:23,879
Come on, don't be so serious.

142
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,039
Look at you now.

143
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,039
You've changed a lot.

144
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:31,360
You used to laugh so hard at bad jokes.

145
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,759
Why do you have so much on your mind now?

146
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,399
That was before.

147
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:38,399
I do miss those times.

148
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,519
But there's no turning back.

149
00:11:42,759 --> 00:11:43,759
Yes, we can.

150
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:46,720
As long as you trust me.

151
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,000
Hello. Can I talk to the person in charge?

152
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,480
Hello, do you have an appointment?

153
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,679
Yes, I'm Hou Jue.

154
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:23,440
Xiao Yue, he's here for me.

155
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,639
Hou Jue, right?

156
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,080
Mr. Xiao?

157
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,279
Zi Heng.

158
00:12:29,279 --> 00:12:30,720
- Hello. - We don't do that here.

159
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,240
- Just call me Zi Heng. - You...

160
00:12:32,639 --> 00:12:33,720
Take a seat.

161
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,720
Welcome to Hedgehog Factory.

162
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,600
You designed this?

163
00:12:38,519 --> 00:12:40,840
It looks like everything but a company.

164
00:12:41,399 --> 00:12:43,600
What you think is what you see.

165
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,720
What would you like to drink?

166
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,080
- Water is fine. - All right.

167
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,480
You said on the phone...

168
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,919
that you were the one who designed the book bar.

169
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:51,919
Yes.

170
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:54,320
I designed it when I was in college.

171
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,600
Have you given it to anyone?

172
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,279
Zhang Sheng.

173
00:12:57,879 --> 00:13:00,360
When I presented my project,

174
00:13:00,879 --> 00:13:01,960
on the day itself,

175
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,519
