184
00:13:22,919 --> 00:13:24,120
It's not that functional either.

185
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,600
It's similar to this office.

186
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,960
The sense of disorder is very strong.

187
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:30,200
And it's easy for people to communicate...

188
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,559
as the area partition isn't so clear.

189
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,639
Thank you for acknowledging my design.

190
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:36,159
Let me tell you, this kind of office...

191
00:13:36,159 --> 00:13:37,759
is where geniuses are born.

192
00:13:37,759 --> 00:13:39,159
That's an overstatement.

193
00:13:39,399 --> 00:13:41,679
I just didn't want to design it...

194
00:13:41,679 --> 00:13:43,240
too much like a company.

195
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,519
This is a place for young people.

196
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:46,519
Young people need energy and passion.

197
00:13:46,639 --> 00:13:47,919
You have to open your mind for that.

198
00:13:47,919 --> 00:13:50,399
When I designed the book bar, I only had one idea.

199
00:13:50,399 --> 00:13:53,320
I wanted the book bar to not look like a book bar.

200
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,279
That was what I loved the most.

201
00:13:55,279 --> 00:13:56,840
The most important part of your design.

202
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,080
But you know what?

203
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,000
That was exactly what Zhang Sheng said to me.

204
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:01,639
When I presented the project,

205
00:14:01,639 --> 00:14:03,759
I told them about the whole concept.

206
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,519
How can you prove...

207
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,519
that you've given this proposal to Zhang Sheng?

208
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,200
I sent him an email.

209
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,360
Here's the email record.

210
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:16,399
My friend introduced me to Zhang Sheng.

211
00:14:17,279 --> 00:14:18,879
Then I went to his company.

212
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,159
He loved the design.

213
00:14:21,519 --> 00:14:22,799
He wanted to sign a contract with me that day.

214
00:14:22,799 --> 00:14:25,039
But something urgent came up, so we couldn't make it.

215
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,080
Look.

216
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:29,360
I emailed the design to him.

217
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,639
When I went to look for him afterward,

218
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:32,440
he had resigned with his entire team.

219
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:35,159
And the company had no idea about my proposal.

220
00:14:36,279 --> 00:14:38,480
Let me tell you. Zhang Sheng interviewed with me.

221
00:14:39,279 --> 00:14:40,519
He brought this design with him.

222
00:14:40,639 --> 00:14:42,679
He said he designed it himself.

223
00:14:43,639 --> 00:14:45,440
While we were discussing it,

224
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,720
the concept didn't match up.

225
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,080
So we didn't collaborate in the end.

226
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:49,279
But I bought the design.

227
00:14:51,759 --> 00:14:53,000
I'll be direct, Hou Jue.

228
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,720
You've met Zhang Sheng.

229
00:14:54,879 --> 00:14:56,279
Comparatively,

230
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,000
I trust you more.

231
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,720
I also trust my instincts.

232
00:15:01,279 --> 00:15:03,600
The next time you come here, organize the details and process...

233
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:05,679
on your computer and sign the papers.

234
00:15:05,679 --> 00:15:06,720
I'll have my company's legal team look into it.

235
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,799
No problem.

236
00:15:07,799 --> 00:15:08,960
- Okay. - No problem.

237
00:15:42,799 --> 00:15:44,720
I want to eat the cheese pudding from this place.

238
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,240
I heard there's a two-hour line.

239
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,279
No way.

240
00:15:47,399 --> 00:15:49,559
At this age, you still eat desserts.

241
00:15:50,919 --> 00:15:52,720
"Dongmen Pedestrian Street."

